What you need to know:

Ms Wahu said they boarded a matatu at Ndururumo terminus to Thika town, where they opened their two wholesale shops at 8am.They used public transport since Gitau’s vehicles were out of petrol, she claimed.But Kiambu Business Community Chairman Alfred Wanyoike disputed the narrative “since all his eight vehicles were in good condition”.Gitau’s mother, Rosemary Wanjiru, 68, the business community and close friends claim there’s bad blood between Ms Wahu and her two co-wives.